# Web Console Reading Rule

When the user asks you to **read the web console**, **export and read the raw web console output**.

## Why

Web console UIs use collapsible rows. Collapsed content is invisible in normal views, so you will miss errors, stack traces, or nested objects. Raw export shows everything.

## What to Do

1. **Export the raw console** (right-click → "Save as..." or use the browser's export/save console feature).
2. **Read the exported file**—do not rely on in-UI copy/paste or screenshots of the console.
3. Use the full raw output for debugging and analysis.

## Do NOT

- Assume you can see everything from the collapsed UI.
- Rely on manually expanded rows—you may miss collapsed entries.
